# Breadcrumb Schema - SERP Display

Use **BreadcrumbList** JSON-LD for SERP breadcrumbs. Plain URL path segments only.

## Critical: NO HOME

**DO NOT add "Home" or root (`/`) to breadcrumb schema.** Never include `{ name: "Home", item: "/" }` in `itemListElement`. This breaks SEO and the user explicitly forbids it. Start breadcrumbs from the first meaningful path segment (e.g. categories, search, slug).

## Rules

- **Plain URL path segments** as `name` (e.g. `"about-us"`, `"blog"`, `"categories"`, `"reactions"`)
- **NEVER include "Home"** or root in `itemListElement` - no exceptions
- **Each page defines its own schema** - no shared schema files, no exports/imports
- Add inline via `<script type="application/ld+json" dangerouslySetInnerHTML={{ __html: JSON.stringify(schema) }} />`

## Pattern

```tsx
// ✅ Correct - no Home
const breadcrumbSchema = {
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "BreadcrumbList",
  itemListElement: [
    { "@type": "ListItem", position: 1, name: "categories", item: `${BASE}/categories` },
    { "@type": "ListItem", position: 2, name: category.name, item: `${BASE}/categories/${slug}` },
  ],
}

// ❌ WRONG - never do this
// { "@type": "ListItem", position: 1, name: "Home", item: `${BASE}/` },
```

Do not touch home page (`app/page.tsx`).
